<br>
In my scenario, FGs aren't reservable.  Nasren has been there for 18 hours, Puma walks in and shouts &quot;camp check!&quot;  Nasren shouts &quot;Ragefire!&quot; and Puma goes to Wakening Lands or something.  2 hours later Ragefire pops.  He calls in his guild, they commit Giant Genocide, and kill Ragefire off too.  Epic done.<br>
<br>
You might suggest that Puma will also sit down in the lair at hour 18.  At hour 20, they both shout to their guilds and a mad dash ensues.  The battle starts, both guilds jump in, one group gets the exp.  Cleric X joins the group real quick, loots the heart, and everyone walks away angry.  While this is possible, I don't think it it will happen!  In general this server is pretty good at walking away when someone is there already.  In particular, I'd point to an example like Lord Grimrot. He is another irritating and long-running quest that clerics do.  Cleric A is sitting at the ruins.  Cleric B walks up, chats for a minute, and then goes on his way.  No hard feelings.<br>
<br>
In my scenario, Ragefire is camped almost constantly.  The Naggy raid ends, and someone shouts, &quot;Ragefire!&quot;.  Or maybe someone has left their monk-alt in the Lair from before the Naggy pop.  In my scenario, the next epic goes to the most masochistic cleric.  This isn't perfect either, but I think the rules are more straightforward and understandable.  They lead to fewer hard feelings.<br>
<br>
In all civility and politeness,<br>
